<recipe xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd">
  <title>Mexican Black Beans and Rice</title>
  <filename>mexican_black_beans_and_rice.xml</filename>
  <thumbnail>mexican_blackbeans_and_rice.jpeg</thumbnail>
  <category>Sides</category>
  <diet>Vegetarian</diet>
  <ingredient>3 cups cooked rice</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 can black beans rinsed</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 can chopped tomatoes </ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 red pepper diced</ingredient>
  <ingredient>3-4 garlic cloves crushed</ingredient>
  <ingredient>2-3 TBsp olive oil</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1/2-1 teasp chilli powder</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1/2-1 teasp paprika </ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 teasp cumin</ingredient>
  <ingredient>2 TBsp oregano </ingredient>
  <ingredient>2 stock cubes</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1/4 cup boiling water</ingredient>
  <ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
  <step>Heat oven to 180C.</step>
  <step>In a large pan that can go in the oven, heat olive oil for 2-3 minutes.</step>
  <step>Once hot cook garlic for 3 minutes, then add red pepper and cook for a further 3 minutes.</step>
  <step>Add stock cubes to boiling water and add it with the rest of the ingredients and stir very well.</step>
  <step>Once all combined place lid on pan and place in oven for 30-40 minutes or until all hot.</step>
  <step>Serve as a side or main.</step>
  <step>This can be doubled if required.</step>
</recipe>
